## 01. SLEEP — Deep & Restorative
### Applied in: PFTE: Insomnia Remedy (Series 01)

### Target State
Deep NREM sleep (Stages 3-4). Delta brainwave dominance.
Reduction of micro-arousals. Continuous 8-9hr sleep cycle maintenance.

### Frequencies That Work

| Frequency / Technique | Effect | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Delta waves (1–3 Hz) | Deep sleep induction. Restorative NREM. | Carrier frequency, not audible directly |
| Theta waves (4–8 Hz) | Light sleep, drowsiness, hypnagogic state | Used in early phases (SIGNAL, INDUCTION) |
| 432 Hz tuning | Believed to lower blood pressure, slow heart rate | Mathematically consistent with natural resonance. Some debate on scientific rigor — use as secondary support, not primary claim |
| Sub-bass carrier (<200 Hz) | Masks environmental noise without broadband noise disruption | The Sub-Veil Filter — PFTE proprietary technique |
| Binaural beats (Delta range) | Brainwave entrainment toward sleep frequencies | Requires headphones for full effect. Effective for sleep onset. |

### Clinical Guardrails — What to Avoid

| Avoid | Reason |
|---|---|
| Pink noise (continuous broadband) | Penn Medicine study: reduces REM sleep, may harm sleep quality and memory consolidation |
| Percussive transients / beats | Activates cognitive rhythm-tracking. Brain stays alert predicting next beat. |
| Frequencies above 8kHz | Alerting effect. PFTE standard: ≤ −60 dB at 8kHz |
| Sudden dynamic shifts | Triggers micro-arousals. LRA target: ≤6.0 LU |
| Binaural beats above Theta range | Alpha and Beta binaural beats are alerting, not sleep-inducing |

