## 02. CHILL / AMBIENT — Relaxed Alertness
### Applied in: PFTE: Drift (Series 02)

### Target State
Relaxed but conscious. Alpha wave dominance.
Not sleep. Not work. The space between.
Reduced cortisol. Lowered cognitive load. Present-moment awareness.

### Frequencies That Work

| Frequency / Technique | Effect | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Alpha waves (8–13 Hz) | Relaxed alertness. Calm without drowsiness. | The "flow state" precursor |
| Low Theta (4–6 Hz) | Deep relaxation, creative daydreaming | Avoid deep Theta — edges into sleep induction |
| 528 Hz (Solfeggio) | Some evidence for stress reduction, ANS regulation | Effect on endocrine system studied. Use as flavor, not foundation. |
| Slow tempo (60–80 BPM) | Synchronizes with resting heart rate | Minimal percussion. No driving rhythms. |
| Natural textures | Rain, water, ambient room tone | Psychologically associated with safety and rest |

### Clinical Guardrails — What to Avoid

| Avoid | Reason |
