## 03. FOCUS / PRODUCTIVITY — Deep Work
### Applied in: PFTE: Work Mode (Series 03 — PLANNED)

### Target State
Sustained cognitive focus. Reduced distraction.
Flow state entry and maintenance.
Low anxiety. High executive function.
Target user: deep work sessions, coding, writing, design, studying.

### Frequencies That Work

| Frequency / Technique | Effect | Evidence Level |
|---|---|---|
| Beta waves (13–30 Hz) | Active thinking, focus, alertness | Strong. Beta dominates during focused cognitive work. |
| Low Beta (13–15 Hz) | Calm focus without anxiety | Sweet spot for sustained work. Avoid high Beta (>25 Hz) — produces anxiety. |
| Gamma waves (30–100 Hz) | Higher cognitive processing, information binding | Emerging research. Associated with peak mental performance. |
| 40 Hz Gamma entrainment | Cognitive enhancement, attention | Active research area. Some evidence for focus and memory. |
| Alpha (8–13 Hz) as baseline | Reduces background anxiety during focus | Used as underlayer. Prevents over-activation. |
| Binaural beats (Beta range) | Entrains brain toward focus frequencies | Requires headphones. More research needed but directionally positive. |
| Brown noise | Masks distraction without alerting effect | Preferred over white noise for focus tasks. Less fatiguing. |
| Isochronic tones (Beta) | Brainwave entrainment without headphones | Does not require stereo separation. More accessible than binaural. |

### Clinical Guardrails — What to Avoid

| Avoid | Reason |
|---|---|
| Delta / deep Theta carriers | Will induce drowsiness. Wrong direction entirely. |
| High Beta (>25 Hz) entrainment | Produces anxiety and cognitive overload |
| Music with lyrics | Language processing competes with reading/writing tasks |
| Dynamic variation / builds | Pulls attention. Focus music must be predictable and stable. |
| Pink noise (prolonged) | REM disruption risk carries over to daytime cognitive recovery |
| Emotionally activating music | Triggers default mode network. Mind wanders. |

### Research To Validate Before Production

These are directions to research — not confirmed PFTE positions yet:

- 40 Hz gamma entrainment and cognitive performance (MIT / Alzheimer's research — check PMC)
- Brown noise vs white noise for cognitive task performance
- Isochronic tones efficacy vs binaural beats for focus
- Optimal session length for focus music (does efficacy decay after 90 min?)
- NASA Task Load Index studies on background music and cognitive load
- Mozart Effect — largely debunked but understand why, for positioning
- The "arousal-mood" hypothesis: music improves performance via mood, not direct neural entrainment

