### Modular Assembly Protocol (for long-form content)

1. Generate components in Suno Pro (max ~150min each)
2. Normalize all components to −22 LUFS before assembly
3. Stitch with 3-second crossfades in Audacity
4. Final Shutter Encoder pass for EBU R128 compliance
5. QC check: ffprobe analysis before upload

### The Zero-Beat Mandate

Applies to all PFTE series.
Absolute removal of percussive transients.
Reason: prevents brain's cognitive rhythm-tracking from maintaining alertness.
Exception: Focus series may introduce very sparse, non-rhythmic tonal events.

### The Sub-Veil Filter (Sleep series only)

Heavy aggressive low-pass filter, cutoff <200 Hz.
Creates muffled auditory blanket.
Blocks environmental noise without broadband noise (which harms REM).
PFTE proprietary technique. Do not apply to non-sleep series.

